						               													<description>A mini-game from the oldschool French magazine Casus Belli (Issue 18 - Dec 1983). In the game, adventurers must seduce the Queen of the Kingdom of Passion and eliminate all others courtiers while controlling military patrols. The game is a mix between roleplaying games and boardgame as each player defines the seduction and discretion score for his character. Several magic items may be found to help him in his mission.&amp;#10;The game can be played by 2 to 4 players.&amp;#10;The game has only 10 counters : 4 characters and 6 patrols.&amp;#10;It needs 2 d6 dices to play.&amp;#10;The games ends when a character has managed to sit on the throne besides the queen and all other players are captured, or it ends when all the characters are captured and remain in the depths of the dungeon.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
